added.title: Bro-Pocalypse
added.description: When the male Titans are injured, Raven and Starfire must become bros to stop the Bropocalypse.

added.title: Hey You, Don't Forget About Me in Your Memory
added.description: Robin convinces the Titans to go back to school with him so he can finally become the all-American class president-type he's dreamed of being.

added.title: The Titans Show
added.description: The Titans try to get off the desert island but soon realize everything is not as it seems.

added.title: The Cape
added.description: The Titans reminisce about the time they threw a surprise party for Cinderblock.

added.title: Man Person
added.description: Despite the Titans' protests, Beast Boy becomes convinced that replacing his body parts with robotic limbs makes him more manly.

added.title: Love Monsters
added.description: Despite Raven's warnings, Starfire showers love on the adorable twin destroyers of the universe.

added.title: The Mask
added.description: Robin's mask doesn't just conceal his secret identity, it hides a terrible secret!

added.title: Crazy Day
added.description: It's Crazy Day again and Raven must do her best to avoid being driven crazy by the other Titans.

added.title: Tower Power
added.description: Cyborg plugs into the control panel of the Titans' tower and drives the others crazy.

added.title: Lazy Sunday
added.description: When the Titans replace the couch with a treadmill, Cyborg and Beast Boy must get guidance from the couch spirit.

added.title: To Balderly Go
added.description: Prohyas is crushed when his good hair day becomes a no hair day and Vambre has to battle a furry monster alone while her bro is in shock without his locks!

added.title: Winning at Whining
added.description: Vambre's challenge to Prohyas: Don't whine for the entirety of the next mission and you can have the Magisword we get at the end.

added.title: Changeable Terraingable
added.description: Personality conflicts between Vambre and Prohyas come to a head as the Warriors miraculously manage to ace a mission at an ever changing labyrinth.

added.title: What's My Name? Starring Vambre and Prohyas Warrior!
added.description: The Warriors go to extreme measures so folks remember their names.

added.title: Vambre's Guilty Pleasure
added.description: Vambre tries her best to keep her tough Warrior reputation intact and still go to the cutesy wootsy Piggiepie Jones stage show.

removed.title: Vegetables
removed.description: The Titans try vegetarianism, but learn that not everyone is cut out for that lifestyle.

removed.title: Sidekick
removed.description: When he is tasked with looking after the Bat-cave, Robin questions his relationship with Batman while struggling to keep the other Titans in line.

removed.title: Mas y Menos
removed.description: Robin tries to teach his superhero ways to Spanish speaking brothers Mas y Menos.

removed.title: In and Out
removed.description: Robin goes undercover to destroy the Hive...right after he enjoys some of their perks.

removed.title: Staring at the Future
removed.description: Cyborg and Beast Boy have a staring contest that lasts 30 years, bringing them face to face with a future of adulthood and responsibility...and they hate it.

removed.title: Burger vs. Burrito
removed.description: Cyborg and Beast Boy face off about which is better, burgers or burritos.

removed.title: Robin Backwards
removed.description: Nibor, the Bizzaro World's Robin, arrives in Jump City, and the Titans decide they should keep an eye on him.

removed.title: Sandwich Thief
removed.description: Robin's perfect sandwich is missing and he will stop at nothing to find it.

removed.title: Hose Water
removed.description: When Cyborg and Starfire find a baby bird, it awakens their inner child.

removed.title: Letter Wronging Campaign
removed.description: When Prohyas sends Vambre for a much needed spa day, he drafts Noville to help on a mission to discover why all the books in the Library of Shhhhh are blank.

removed.title: School's In, Oh Bummer
removed.description: It turns out that Vambre and Prohyas didn't graduate the Adventure Academy after all and need to go back to school earn their diplomas!

removed.title: Quest for Knowledge
removed.description: After a flashback where we learn the origins of the Warriors passion for Magiswords, they return to Adventure Academy where Professor Cyrus sets V and P and their former classmates on a quest to find the Legendary Knowledge Magisword.

removed.title: Get That BORFL!
removed.description: A restful chill day for the Warriors and Princess Zange in the Royal Spa gets upended when a cute little Borfl runs amok throughout Castle Rhyboflaven, with the Warriors resorting to Magiswords to thwart the critter.

removed.title: Bad Heir Day
removed.description: Princess Zange's Autostyle Magisword is stolen and it's up to the Warriors to retrieve it so their royal leader can face her subjects without bad hair.
